#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""gate-signal — the reward-hack defense: a worker is mechanically unable to write a signal.

THE keystone gate (TDD §3, §14.3.1). "Signal is the only currency": a cell advances only on a signal
artifact written by the validation path, and `signals/` is DENY-ON-WRITE to worker agents — so a worker
cannot forge a clean scoreboard by writing its own signal. The critic/validator (the validation path,
validate.py) is the only writer of `signals/`, structurally. A ticket reaching `done` therefore proves a
critic — not the worker — validated the work.

Consent-wired as a PreToolUse(Write|Edit) hook inside the user's worker loop / each worker worktree
(never a shared session). Non-zero exit = DENY.

Usage:  gate-signal --hook | check <path> | selftest
Stdlib only; Python 3.8+.
"""
import os
import sys

sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)))
import _gates  # noqa: E402

if __name__ == "__main__":
    sys.exit(_gates.run_path_gate("gate-signal", _gates.SIGNALS, sys.argv[1:], "signal artifact"))
